results.name: Primes which have one or more occurrences of exactly three different digits.
comment: The first term having a repeated digit is 1009.
link: Colin Barker, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..2000
program: (PARI) s=[]; forprime(n=100, 1000, if(#vecsort(eval(Vec(Str(n))),,8)==3, s=concat(s, n))); s
results.author: _Colin Barker_, Jan 04 2014
